WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:21.640
The Well by Claire Harris

00:21.640 --> 00:23.520
It is summer.

00:23.520 --> 00:25.920
The air is hot.

00:25.920 --> 00:29.960
It is hot inside Leah's house.

00:29.960 --> 00:36.640
Leah lives with her mother, her father, and her brother Jay.

00:36.640 --> 00:40.280
Her grandmother lives with them too.

00:40.280 --> 00:44.280
Leah's grandmother is old and sick.

00:44.280 --> 00:47.640
She lies in her bed all day.

00:47.640 --> 00:50.360
The old woman is sad.

00:50.360 --> 00:53.200
Her husband is dead.

00:53.200 --> 00:56.200
She often talks to his photograph.

00:56.640 --> 00:59.160
Yes, husband.

00:59.160 --> 01:02.800
Oh, it's in the well.

01:02.800 --> 01:06.000
It's in a bucket of water.

01:06.000 --> 01:08.720
Thank you.

01:08.720 --> 01:13.080
Leah and her mother are in grandmother's room.

01:13.080 --> 01:16.800
Leah's mother brings some food and water.

01:16.800 --> 01:22.240
Please, go to the well, says grandmother.

01:22.320 --> 01:27.680
Bring me some water in the bucket.

01:27.680 --> 01:31.160
There is no well here, Mar.

01:31.160 --> 01:33.280
Says Leah's mother.

01:33.280 --> 01:36.360
You live in the town now.

01:36.360 --> 01:38.840
We have good water.

01:38.840 --> 01:42.560
It comes from the tap.

01:42.560 --> 01:47.200
Leah's mother speaks quietly to her daughter.

01:47.200 --> 01:50.880
Grandmother is sick, she says.

01:50.880 --> 01:55.360
She is not thinking clearly.

01:55.360 --> 01:59.800
Leah's mother gives the old woman some water.

01:59.800 --> 02:04.760
No, no, says grandmother.

02:04.760 --> 02:09.680
Go to the farm's well.

02:09.680 --> 02:14.560
We must not visit the old farm now, Mar.

02:14.560 --> 02:16.600
Leah's mother says.

02:16.600 --> 02:19.960
The farm is near the volcano.

02:19.960 --> 02:23.160
The volcano is dangerous.

02:23.160 --> 02:25.960
There is fire and smoke.

02:25.960 --> 02:30.440
Soldiers are guarding the roads.

02:30.440 --> 02:32.880
Grandmother doesn't hear her.

02:32.880 --> 02:36.120
Go to the well.

02:36.120 --> 02:38.480
Grandmother says again.

02:38.480 --> 02:41.680
Bring me the bucket of water.

02:41.680 --> 02:44.640
Please hurry.

02:44.640 --> 02:46.000
I'll go.

02:46.000 --> 02:47.600
Says Leah.

02:47.600 --> 02:49.960
I'll walk to the farm.

02:49.960 --> 02:52.880
I know the way.

02:52.880 --> 02:57.680
Leah tells her father and brother about the well.

02:57.680 --> 03:00.680
Leah, you mustn't visit the farm.

03:00.680 --> 03:03.640
The volcano is near the farm.

03:03.640 --> 03:07.960
The volcano is dangerous.

03:07.960 --> 03:10.160
I'll go with Leah.

03:10.160 --> 03:15.040
We'll get the water for grandmother.

03:15.040 --> 03:19.920
The next morning, Leah and Jay get up early.

03:19.920 --> 03:24.200
Leah puts some bread and a sausage in her bag.

03:24.200 --> 03:30.200
She puts a bottle of water in the bag too.

03:30.200 --> 03:33.320
Jay and Leah are on the highway.

03:33.320 --> 03:35.280
The air is hot.

03:35.280 --> 03:39.160
The air is full of dust.

03:39.160 --> 03:43.800
At the checkpoint, Leah and Jay meet a soldier.

03:43.800 --> 03:45.760
She talks to them.

03:45.760 --> 03:49.880
The volcano isn't dangerous today.

03:49.880 --> 03:53.880
We're going to our grandmother's farm.

03:53.880 --> 03:55.720
She's sick.

03:55.720 --> 03:58.640
She wants water from the well.

03:58.640 --> 04:01.600
It will cure her sickness.

04:01.600 --> 04:04.640
You're going to get some magic water.

04:04.640 --> 04:07.800
Bring me some too.

04:07.800 --> 04:11.360
Leah and Jay stop next to a bridge.

04:11.360 --> 04:14.240
They eat their lunch.

04:14.240 --> 04:17.840
There is a small house next to the bridge.

04:17.840 --> 04:20.800
A friendly woman lives there.

04:20.800 --> 04:23.960
She talks to Jay and Leah.

04:23.960 --> 04:26.280
She has a small dog.

04:26.280 --> 04:29.840
It is a small red dog.

04:29.840 --> 04:32.520
Jay gives the dog some sausage.

04:32.520 --> 04:35.680
Where are you going?

04:35.680 --> 04:37.320
The woman asks.

04:37.320 --> 04:41.120
It is a hot day.

04:41.120 --> 04:44.000
We're going to our grandmother's farm.

04:44.000 --> 04:45.800
Jay replies.

04:45.800 --> 04:47.680
She is sick.

04:47.680 --> 04:51.080
She wants water from the well.

04:51.080 --> 04:53.680
Take some water from my well.

04:53.680 --> 04:55.160
It's good.

04:55.160 --> 04:58.960
It's good fresh water.

04:58.960 --> 05:01.800
That's a good idea, Leah.

05:01.800 --> 05:04.320
It's a very hot day.

05:04.320 --> 05:07.600
I don't want to walk anymore.

05:07.680 --> 05:09.280
OK, Jay.

05:09.280 --> 05:11.360
Stay here.

05:11.360 --> 05:13.640
I will go to the farm alone.

05:16.520 --> 05:18.920
Leah walks on.

05:18.920 --> 05:22.480
After a minute, Jay follows her.

05:22.480 --> 05:25.320
They walk and they walk.

05:25.320 --> 05:27.920
There are no houses here.

05:27.920 --> 05:30.240
There are no animals.

05:30.240 --> 05:35.040
There is dry grass and there is dust.

05:35.040 --> 05:37.640
They hear a sound.

05:37.640 --> 05:39.880
What is that sound?

05:39.880 --> 05:41.760
Jay asks.

05:41.760 --> 05:44.720
Is someone calling us?

05:44.720 --> 05:46.680
No.

05:46.680 --> 05:49.440
It's the sound of the wind.

05:49.440 --> 05:51.320
Leah replies.

05:51.320 --> 05:52.560
No.

05:52.560 --> 05:54.960
It isn't the wind.

05:54.960 --> 05:57.160
It's a ghost.

05:57.160 --> 06:00.160
I'm afraid of ghosts.

06:00.160 --> 06:04.000
There are no ghosts here.

06:04.000 --> 06:07.240
Leah and Jay are at the farm.

06:07.240 --> 06:10.520
Jay sees oranges on a tree.

06:10.520 --> 06:13.840
He doesn't see any ghosts.

06:13.840 --> 06:16.040
He pulls some oranges from the tree.

06:18.760 --> 06:21.960
Leah and Jay find the well.

06:21.960 --> 06:24.680
Its cover is broken.

06:24.680 --> 06:27.600
Jay lifts the cover.

06:27.600 --> 06:31.040
The water doesn't smell good.

06:31.120 --> 06:32.920
Ugh.

06:32.920 --> 06:35.960
This water is bad, Leah.

06:35.960 --> 06:38.120
Jay says.

06:38.120 --> 06:41.960
We must take some water for grandmother.

06:41.960 --> 06:44.000
Leah replies.

06:44.000 --> 06:47.640
We must get the bucket.

06:47.640 --> 06:51.480
We must pull this rope.

06:51.480 --> 06:53.680
They hold the rope.

06:53.680 --> 06:56.800
They pull and they pull.

06:56.800 --> 07:00.440
The bucket is very heavy.

07:00.440 --> 07:04.720
At last, the bucket is out of the well.

07:04.720 --> 07:08.280
It is full of dirty water.

07:08.280 --> 07:11.400
Leah empties the bucket.

07:11.400 --> 07:13.680
Jay and Leah have a surprise.

07:22.560 --> 07:24.680
Gold.

07:24.680 --> 07:28.840
These are gold coins.

07:28.840 --> 07:30.600
Yes.

07:30.600 --> 07:33.080
I remember these.

07:33.080 --> 07:37.960
They are grandfather's coins.

07:37.960 --> 07:41.560
Leah and Jay are carrying the bucket.

07:41.560 --> 07:43.440
It is heavy.

07:43.440 --> 07:46.680
There are lots of oranges in the bucket.

07:46.680 --> 07:51.680
The gold coins are under the oranges.

07:51.680 --> 07:56.680
Jay and Leah meet a gang of boys near the bridge.

07:56.680 --> 07:59.280
What's in your bucket?

07:59.280 --> 08:01.640
The boys shout.

08:01.640 --> 08:03.880
Ah, oranges.

08:03.880 --> 08:06.560
Give them to us.

08:06.560 --> 08:10.360
The small red dog runs out of the house.

08:10.360 --> 08:13.120
He barks at the gang of boys.

08:13.120 --> 08:16.560
He barks and he barks.

08:16.560 --> 08:20.120
The friendly woman comes out of the house.

08:20.120 --> 08:23.600
The boys run away.

08:23.600 --> 08:26.880
Jay and Leah are at the checkpoint.

08:26.880 --> 08:30.200
The soldier looks in the bucket.

08:30.200 --> 08:33.800
You don't have any magic water?

08:33.800 --> 08:35.360
No.

08:35.360 --> 08:37.600
We have some magic oranges.

08:42.200 --> 08:46.480
Leah and Jay give the soldier some oranges.

08:46.480 --> 08:48.200
The soldier smiles at them.

08:49.200 --> 08:52.200
Leah and Jay are at home now.

08:52.200 --> 08:55.200
Their grandmother is lying in her bed.

08:55.200 --> 08:59.200
Is that my bucket of water?

08:59.200 --> 09:01.200
No.

09:01.200 --> 09:06.200
It's grandfather's gold.

09:06.200 --> 09:11.200
Everybody laughs.

09:11.200 --> 09:14.200
They are very happy.

09:14.200 --> 09:17.200
Grandmother looks at her husband's photo.

09:17.200 --> 09:19.200
She smiles.

09:19.200 --> 09:23.200
Suddenly they hear a sound.

09:23.200 --> 09:26.200
Is it the sound of the wind?

